%python

# imports
import warnings
import oml
import pandas

# settings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')
pandas.set_option('display.width', 2000)

%python

# sync proxy objects
TF_WIP_PG_METRICS = oml.sync(table="TF_WIP_PG_METRICS")

# pull data
data = {}
data['TF_WIP_PG_METRICS'] = TF_WIP_PG_METRICS.pull()

%python

# prepare data
TF_WIP_CL_CYCLES_IN = oml.push(data['TF_WIP_PG_METRICS'][['COMPANYID','SCORE_CYC1','SCORE_CYC2','SCORE_CYC3']])
TF_WIP_CL_CENTRAL_IN = oml.push(data['TF_WIP_PG_METRICS'][['COMPANYID','SCORE_BCEN','SCORE_CCEN']])

# build models
try:
    oml.drop(model="TF_WIP_CL_CYCLES")
    oml.drop(model="TF_WIP_CL_CENTRAL")
except:
    pass
setting = {'KMNS_ITERATIONS':100, 'KMNS_RANDOM_SEED':6}           
TF_WIP_CL_CYCLES = oml.km(n_clusters=5, **setting).fit(TF_WIP_CL_CYCLES_IN, case_id='COMPANYID', model_name="TF_WIP_CL_CYCLES")
TF_WIP_CL_CENTRAL = oml.km(n_clusters=5, **setting).fit(TF_WIP_CL_CENTRAL_IN, case_id='COMPANYID', model_name="TF_WIP_CL_CENTRAL")

%python

# helpers
def recode_values_for_columns(df, cols):
    for col in cols:
        labels, uniques = pandas.factorize(df[col])
        mapping = {label:f'Cluster #{index+1}' for index, label in enumerate(uniques)}
        df[col] = df[col].replace(mapping)
    return df
    
# pull data
data['TF_WIP_CL_CYCLES_PR'] = TF_WIP_CL_CYCLES_PR.pull()
data['TF_WIP_CL_CENTRAL_PR'] = TF_WIP_CL_CENTRAL_PR.pull()

# transform data 'RESULTS'
data['TF_WIP_CL_RESULTS'] = pandas.merge(data['TF_WIP_CL_CYCLES_PR'], data['TF_WIP_CL_CENTRAL_PR'], left_on=['COMPANYID'], right_on=['COMPANYID'], how='inner')
data['TF_WIP_CL_RESULTS'] = data['TF_WIP_CL_RESULTS'].rename(columns={'CLUSTER_ID_x':'CLUSTER_CYC','CLUSTER_ID_y':'CLUSTER_CEN'})
data['TF_WIP_CL_RESULTS'] = data['TF_WIP_CL_RESULTS'][['COMPANYID','SCORE_CYC1','SCORE_CYC2','SCORE_CYC3','SCORE_BCEN','SCORE_CCEN','CLUSTER_CYC','CLUSTER_CEN']]
data['TF_WIP_CL_RESULTS'] = recode_values_for_columns(data['TF_WIP_CL_RESULTS'], ['CLUSTER_CYC','CLUSTER_CEN'])

# check
z.show(data['TF_WIP_CL_RESULTS'])
